Barclay Brothers Win Control of Maybourne Hotels, Mail Reports

-- B y   E r i k   L a r s o n
-- 
2011-02-27T15:29:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-27/barclay-brothers-win-control-of-maybourne-hotels-mail-reports.html
David and Frederick Barclay, the
brothers who own the Telegraph Media Group, have won control of
Maybourne Hotels Ltd., the  Mail on Sunday  said, without saying
where it got the information.  The siblings agreed to buy 35 percent of the company from
Irish real-estate entrepreneur Derek Quinlan, increasing their
stake to 60 percent, the newspaper reported.  Maybourne, owner of  London ’s Claridge’s, Berkeley and
Connaught hotels, had drawn separate bids of 1 billion pounds
($1.6 billion) each from Qatar Holdings LLC and the Chinese
government, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Larson in London at 
 elarson4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at 
 aaarons@bloomberg.net  